The article discusses Executive Order 13511, issued by President Barack Obama on September 29, 2009, which continues the existence of certain federal advisory committees. The order lists thirteen advisory committees that are continued until September 30, 2011. These committees cover a range of areas including the preservation of the White House, infrastructure, occupational safety and health, historically black colleges and universities, tribal colleges and universities, arts and humanities, international labor organizations, national science, physical fitness and sports, science and technology, export, national security telecommunications, and trade and environment policy. The order also states that the functions of the President under the Federal Advisory Committee Act will be performed by the head of the department or agency designated after each committee, in accordance with established guidelines and procedures. This order supersedes certain sections of a previous executive order. The order is effective from September 30, 2009.